  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "WSQoEwmiH0iqMttQtFGeJG3JSEs=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:46.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Three-tier structure\n\n### 1. User Manifest\n- Topic: `keccak256(\"ph:v2:user:\" + ownerAddress)`\n- One per user, keyed by Ethereum address.\n- Contents: `{ address, drives: { [driveId]: { name, preferredEditor, documentIds, lastUpdated } }, documents, stamps }`.\n- Acts as the discovery index used on recovery.\n\n### 2. Drive Manifest\n- Topic: `keccak256(\"ph:v2:drive:\" + driveId)`\n- One per drive.\n- Contents: `{ driveId, name, preferredEditor, documents: { [docId]: { documentType, name, parentFolder? } }, folders: { [folderId]: { name, parentFolder } } }`.\n- Lets recovery reconstruct folder topology without replaying ops first.\n\n### 3. Document Manifest\n- Topic: `keccak256(\"ph:v2:doc:\" + docId)`\n- One per document.\n- Contents: `{ documentId, documentType, operationBatches: [{ reference, scope, startIndex, endIndex }], latestRevision: { document, global }, keyframes }`.\n- `reference` is the content hash of an encrypted `OperationWithContext[]` payload stored at `/bytes`.\n\n### Deterministic topics\n\nBecause topics are hashes of stable strings, any client with the owner's address can find any drive without external coordination \u2014 the key to serverless recovery.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:46.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:46.000Z"
    }
  },
